@startuml A3_layer_knowledge_data_detailed
title Knowledge/Data Layer – Detailed View

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #000000
  BorderThickness 1
}

package "Knowledge/Data Layer - Storage" as KNOWLEDGE_LAYER {
  
  rectangle "**Relational Database**\nPostgres" as RELATIONAL_DB {
    rectangle "**Application Data**\n• Users & sessions\n• Conversation state\n• Checkpoints" as APP_DATA
    rectangle "**Enrollment Domain Data**\n• Courses & sections\n• Students & enrollments\n• Majors, minors, concentrations\n• Prerequisites & requirements" as ENROLLMENT_DATA
    rectangle "**Financial Data**\n• Tuition & fees\n• Course costs\n• Housing & commuting\n• Financial aid" as FINANCIAL_DATA
  }
  
  rectangle "**Vector Store**\nPostgres + pgvector" as VECTOR_STORE {
    rectangle "• Policy documents\n• Course descriptions\n• Vector embeddings\n• Similarity indices" as VECTOR_CORE
  }
  
  rectangle "**Knowledge Graph**\nNeo4j" as KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH {
    rectangle "• Prerequisites graph\n• Requirements graph\n• Transfer equivalencies\n• Course relationships" as GRAPH_CORE
  }
}

' Services that use this layer
cloud "Agent Service\n(Layer 2 - Port 8000)" as AGENT_SERVICE
cloud "RAG Service\n(Layer 2 - Port 8080)" as RAG_SERVICE
cloud "Enrollment Service\n(Layer 2 - Port 8090)" as ENROLLMENT_SERVICE
cloud "OpenAI\nEmbeddings API" as OPENAI

' Agent Service uses Application Data
AGENT_SERVICE --> APP_DATA : sessions, users, checkpoints

' RAG Service uses Vector Store & Graph
RAG_SERVICE --> OPENAI : generate embeddings
RAG_SERVICE --> VECTOR_STORE : policy documents + vectors
RAG_SERVICE --> KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH : prerequisites, requirements

' Enrollment Service uses Enrollment & Financial Data
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> ENROLLMENT_DATA : query courses, enrollments, requirements
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> FINANCIAL_DATA : query tuition, fees, costs
ENROLLMENT_SERVICE --> KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH : query prerequisites, requirements graph

note bottom of RELATIONAL_DB
**Relational Database** (Postgres)
**Application Data:**
- Users, sessions, auth
- Checkpoints (LangGraph)

**Enrollment Domain Data:**
- Courses, sections, enrollments
- Majors, minors, concentrations
- Prerequisites, requirements
- Students, instructors

**Financial Data:**
- Tuition rates, fees
- Course costs (books, materials)
- Housing, commuting costs
- Financial aid
end note

note bottom of VECTOR_STORE
**Vector Store**
Same Postgres + pgvector extension
- Document chunks (text)
- Vector embeddings
- Similarity search
end note

note bottom of KNOWLEDGE_GRAPH
**Knowledge Graph**
Separate Neo4j instance
- Prerequisites graph (course → course)
- Requirements graph (course → major/minor/concentration)
- Transfer equivalency mappings
- Course relationships (co-requisites, conflicts)
- Graph traversal for enrollment assistance
end note

@enduml


